            <title>[DERBY-2723]  Set correct collation type and derivation for result from user defined functions&apos; that return character string type.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2723</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per the wiki page &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/db-derby/BuiltInLanguageBasedOrderingDERBY-1478&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/db-derby/BuiltInLanguageBasedOrderingDERBY-1478&lt;/a&gt;, assign correct collation type for results of user defined functions. The rule as copied from the wiki page is as follows&lt;br/&gt;
7)For user defined functions&apos; that return character string type, the return type&apos;s collation will have the same collation as of the character set of the schema that the function is defined in. The collation derivation will be implicit. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
